{"type":"message","id":"967a79cf","parentId":"4f254eae","timestamp":"2026-04-20T09:10:56.089Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the setup. The backup runs daily at 3 AM via cron. The script is at `/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace/skills/openclaw-backup/backup.sh`.\n\nTo send a Feishu message after completion, I need to add a notification step at the end of the script. Since OpenClaw has a Feishu integration already set up, I can use it to send a message.\n\nThe simplest approach would be to add a `openclaw send` or similar command at the end of the backup script to notify via Feishu. Let me check what tools are available for sending Feishu messages from the command line.\n\nActually, looking at the skills available, there's a `feishu-im-read` skill but not a direct send skill listed. But since OpenClaw is running and connected to Feishu, there might be a way to send messages through the CLI.\n\n\nI should look for an `openclaw send` command or check the openclaw docs to see how to send messages directly from the script once the backup completes."},{"type":"text","text":"找到了！每天凌晨 3 点跑备份，脚本在 `~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/openclaw-backup/backup.sh`。\n\n要在完成后推送飞书消息，最简单的方案是在脚本末尾加一行通知。让我看看怎么发飞书消息。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_8a34c590fadc41c3a1179990","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw help 2>&1 | grep -i send; openclaw message --help 2>&1 | head -20"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776676246919,"responseId":"0635209776b509d4092dfde67d32a932"}}
