{"type":"message","id":"36e6018b","parentId":"602d5ad2","timestamp":"2026-04-20T09:13:31.606Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the Feishu app credentials. But instead of calling the API directly, let me think about the simplest way to add a notification to the backup script.\n\nLooking at the backup script, it's a simple bash script running via cron at 0 3 * * *. The simplest way to send a Feishu message after completion would be to use the Feishu API directly via curl in the script.\n\nBut I need to send a message to the user HALEI directly. Their OpenID is `ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb`.\n\nThe Feishu API to send a message to a user would be:\n- POST to https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/im/v1/messages\n- With open_id type and the user's open_id\n\n\n- Using the app's access token for authentication\n\nI could leverage the existing plugin credentials (appId and appSecret) to get an access token, then send the message directly via curl. The challenge is that this requires handling OAuth token acquisition and API calls within the bash script, which adds complexity. Alternatively, I could use the openclaw CLI if it supports sending messages, though the help commands seem to hang. Looking at the cron entry, the script runs daily at 3 AM with output logged to a file.\n\nThe simplest solution is to add curl commands directly in the backup script after the push completes. I need to get an access token from the Feishu API using the app credentials, then send a message to the user. Let me write the code to handle this."},{"type":"text","text":"找到了。备份脚本末尾已经有 git push，现在只需要在成功推送后加一行发飞书消息。方案是在脚本里用 curl 调用飞书 API 直接发消息给你（OpenID: ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb）。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_93f259be86ab4137b021be8b","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"tail -15 /home/halei/.openclaw/workspace/skills/openclaw-backup/backup.sh"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"inpu