{"type":"message","id":"adc97334","parentId":"28cdbc5a","timestamp":"2026-04-20T09:20:39.830Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_06a64c5611e14aa9aa76cf00","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# MEMORY.md - 选品专家长期记忆\n\n## 业务定位\n专注 **TikTok Shop 东南亚发饰选品**，主力市场 **越南（VN）为主，泰国（TH）为辅**，主营品类：发夹、发箍、发圈、头绳、抓夹、发簪。\n\n## 核心理念（亚声精铺模式）\n- 重选品、轻运营\n- 少而精，每月 5-10 款\n- 综合评分 ≥80 才上架\n- 数据驱动，避免主观判断\n\n## ⭐ 三大核心打法\n\n### 1. 变体堆叠（评论共享）\n发饰天然适合：颜色5-10色、规格3+种、套装2+形式\n→ 5个颜色变体只算一个链接，评论全部累计\n\n### 2. 季节性+节日性\n- 旺季同一起跑线，不拼老链接权重\n- 越南节日：春节(1-2月)、情人节(2月)、妇女节(3月)、国庆(9.2)、圣诞(12月)\n- 提前45-60天上架\n\n### 3. 套装化高客单价\n- 单件¥3-8 → 套装翻2-5倍\n- 套装毛利率应≥40%\n\n## 数据源\n- **EchoTik**（echotik.live）：TikTok 商品销量/GMV/达人数据\n- **1688**：供应链查价\n- **Google Trends**：趋势验证"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":64,"aggregated":"# MEMORY.md - 选品专家长期记忆\n\n## 业务定位\n专注 **TikTok Shop 东南亚发饰选品**，主力市场 **越南（VN）为主，泰国（TH）为辅**，主营品类：发夹、发箍、发圈、头绳、抓夹、发簪。\n\n## 核心理念（亚声精铺模式）\n- 重选品、轻运营\n- 少而精，每月 5-10 款\n- 综合评分 ≥80 才上架\n- 数据驱动，避免主观判断\n\n## ⭐ 三大核心打法\n\n### 1. 变体堆叠（评论共享）\n发饰天然适合：颜色5-10色、规格3+种、套装2+形式\n→ 5个颜色变体只算一个链接，评论全部累计\n\n### 2. 季节性+节日性\n- 旺季同一起跑线，不拼老链接权重\n- 越南节日：春节(1-2月)、情人节(2月)、妇女节(3月)、国庆(9.2)、圣诞(12月)\n- 提前45-60天上架\n\n### 3. 套装化高客单价\n- 单件¥3-8 → 套装翻2-5倍\n- 套装毛利率应≥40%\n\n## 数据源\n- **EchoTik**（echotik.live）：TikTok 商品销量/GMV/达人数据\n- **1688**：供应链查价\n- **Google Trends**：趋势验证","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776676839815}}
{"type":"message","id":"714821cd","parentId":"adc97334","timestamp":"2026-04-20T09:20:53.940Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture. Let me summarize:\n\n**Current Memory Architecture:**\n1. **memory-core** - official file-based memory (plugin enabled in `slots`)\n2. **memory-lancedb** - disabled (not in `slots.allow`)\n3. **openViking** - registered as a context-engine hook but remote service not running (port 1933 not listening), LanceDB has 0 chunks\n\n**Three memory layers (pure file-based):**\n- Short-term: current session context\n- Medium-term: `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` daily files\n- Long-term: `MEMORY.md` curated memories\n\n\n- **Selector Agent (tts)** has its own workspace at `~/.openclaw/workspace/Selector/` with independent memory files, while **product-selector** doesn't have its own separate configuration. The key thing is that memory-search is configured with Gemini as the provider, and the Selector's three-layer memory structure is already set up.\n\n- The 4.12 switch to OpenViking appears to have left it non-functional (port 1933 not listening, LanceDB empty), but since memory-core is file-based and the search provider is set to Gemini, the system is actually operating on pure file memory with cloud search capabilities rather than relying on OpenViking's local vector store.\n\n- The Selector workspace has its own complete memory system, and while the 4.18 dream file shows configuration changes for product-selector and tts agent, I need to verify if those changes persisted after the OpenViking migration. The user is asking whether the Evo project from two days ago is actually functioning, so I should clarify what's actually running versus what was configured."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_8fbddd8624d644fdbd08e158","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/ | sort"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_66aaa1e0bf424c77b0aa5200","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat